# Airline Booking System

A Django-based web application for managing flights, bookings, and customers for a private aircraft charter service.

## Overview

This application allows management of a fleet of private jets and provides functionality for customers to book flights between various destinations. The system tracks aircraft details, airport information, routes, flight schedules, and customer data.

## Features

- Aircraft fleet management
- Airport database
- Flight scheduling and route management
- Customer registration and management
- Booking system with automated pricing
- User-friendly web interface

## Technologies

- Python 3.x
- Django 4.x
- HTML/CSS
- JavaScript
- SQLite (development) / PostgreSQL (production)

## Installation

1. Clone the repository
   ```
   git clone https://github.com/yourusername/airline-booking-system.git
   cd airline-booking-system
   ```

2. Create and activate a virtual environment
   ```
   python -m venv venv
   source venv/bin/activate  # On Windows, use: venv\Scripts\activate
   ```

3. Install dependencies
   ```
   pip install -r requirements.txt
   ```

4. Run migrations
   ```
   python manage.py migrate
   ```

5. Create a superuser
   ```
   python manage.py createsuperuser
   ```

6. Run the development server
   ```
   python manage.py runserver
   ```

## Project Structure

The project is organized into the following main components:

- Models: Defines the database schema for flights, aircraft, customers, etc.
- Views: Handles HTTP requests and responses
- Templates: Renders HTML pages for the user interface
- URLs: Maps URLs to views

## Current Status

This project is currently in development. The following components have been implemented:
- Database models for core functionality
- Basic views started


